Pour the @water{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{}, along with a pinch of @salt{}, and
bring to the boil on high heat. Roughly chop the @chestnut mushrooms{150}(roughly chopped)
and the @coriander{1/2%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Cut the
@British chicken thighs{3} into 3cm chunks. Cut the @lime{1/2} into wedges.

When the water is boiling, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium
and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from
the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until
ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam). In a #mixing bowl{},
combine the @cornflour{20%g} with a pinch of @salt{} and a few grinds of @ground black pepper{}.
Add the chicken and coat thoroughly. Leave to one side.

Place a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @cashew pieces{25} (no oil!) and
toast until golden brown, shaking the pan constantly, about ~{5%minutes}.

> Watch the nuts like a hawk as they can burn easily.

Remove the cashews from the pan and set aside.

Add a splash of @oil{} to the now empty frying pan and place on high heat. Once the
oil is really hot add the chicken and fry until golden brown all over, then remove and
set aside, about ~{5%minutes}.

> Cook in batches if you have a small pan.

Once again return the empty frying pan to medium-high heat and add another splash of
oil along with the @Massaman curry paste{25%g}.

> If you don't want it spicy then add a little less.

Stir the curry paste for ~{1%minute}, then add the @coconut milk{200%ml},
chicken and mushrooms. Once the coconut milk comes to the boil, stir in the
@peanut butter{1%tbsp} and turn the heat to low. Gently simmer, until the chicken
is cooked through, ~{10%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and add it to the curry. Gently fold the rice and
three-quarters of the coriander into the sauce. Squeeze over the juice of some of
the lime. Serve in #bowls{} and garnish with the remaining coriander, the cashews and
any lime wedges if you have left. Enjoy!